<i>adverb</i>: 어엿이 [어여시], 변변히 [변변히], 번듯이 [번드시], 버젓이 [버저시] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>어엿이 [어여시]</dt><br>
<dd>respectably; decently</dd><br>
<dd>태도가 아주 번듯하고 당당하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being decent and dignified in one's attitude.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>변변히 [변변히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. respectably</dd><br>
<dd>사람의 생김새나 됨됨이 등이 보통을 넘게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state where one's appearance, personality, etc., are at a higher level than normal.</dd><br>
<dd>2. enough</dd><br>
<dd>인사나 옷, 음식 등이 제대로 갖추어져 충분하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which salutation, clothes, food, etc., have been prepared properly and sufficiently.</dd><br>
<dd>3. decently</dd><br>
<dd>집안이나 실력 등이 남보다 못하지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which one's family or ability, etc., are not below that of others.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>번듯이 [번드시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. in a balance</dd><br>
<dd>큰 물체가 기울어지거나 굽지 않고 바르게.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a large object being straight without being tilted or bent.</dd><br>
<dd>2. in a good look</dd><br>
<dd>생김새가 단정하고 훤하게.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing an appearance being tidy and handsome.</dd><br>
<dd>3. decently</dd><br>
<dd>형편이나 지위, 권세 등이 버젓하고 당당하게.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a situation, position, power, etc., being fair and open.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>버젓이 [버저시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. brazenly; shamelessly; overtly</dd><br>
<dd>남의 시선을 신경 써서 조심하지 않고 뻔뻔하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of being careless and bold-faced without being self-conscious.</dd><br>
<dd>2. decently; presentably</dd><br>
<dd>남에게 뒤지지 않을 정도로 번듯하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being so respectable as to be second to none.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>